Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
General case: Amplitude & Phase difference at difference central frequencies\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8720010610340633`*^9, 
  3.872001100129839*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"15b102df-9a72-4567-abb5-\
15aa01db83c2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The full derivation for this case is relatively involved but follows the \
same template as the simple case. The difference in the current derivation is \
to write each field as a complex amplitude times the carrier with different \
complex amplitudes and different central frequencies:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["E", "j"], "(", "t", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["A", "j"], "(", "t", ")"}], 
     SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
      RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "j"], "t"}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"29e6971a-a034-47b0-b59d-00d7ae82231f"],
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{" ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"j", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ",", "2"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "31d0c227-c99d-4b40-9c2f-9aa03d007ac0"],
 "\n\nThe result of Fourier transforming the cross-correlation between two \
electric fields is\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "~"], "(", "\[Omega]", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"C", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "(", "\[Omega]", ")"}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
       RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "1"]}], ")"}], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "2"]}], ")"}], "*"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "1"]}], ")"}], "*"], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "2"]}], ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"06817ff8-58a1-47b5-a7ed-291891aa8ee9"],
 "\n\nThis is the general result that admits different spectral amplitudes \
and center frequencies. Now, for instance, if ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "1"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "2"], "\[Congruent]", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "09aeeef0-3ae0-456d-8e54-435c34f6c5bb"],
 "\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "~"], "(", "\[Omega]", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"C", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "(", "\[Omega]", ")"}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
       RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "*"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "*"], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"2dccbbe6-b64b-412a-bacf-dd166aa9b651"],
 "\n\nand even more specifically if \t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "\[Congruent]", 
     OverscriptBox["A", "~"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c2b4991a-14e3-4579-bb90-72eb20068b62"],
 "\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     OverscriptBox[
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], "~"], "(", "\[Omega]", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"C", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "(", "\[Omega]", ")"}]}], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
       RowBox[{
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "(", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], 
      "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
       RowBox[{
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], 
      "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c04b8e47-ad84-4fb3-9669-eeb9a77a5d3c"],
 "\n\nIn this last, illustrative case, we see a spike at DC and then two AC \
terms with one reversed along the \[Omega]-axis. Both terms appear at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0d1809d0-5d88-4475-90d3-2a37183cdb92"],
 ", one at a positive frequency and one at a negative frequency. In the \
general case, the appearance of terms that go like ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "2"]}], ")"}], "*"], 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
     RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "1"]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"198c1326-d6c6-4c06-b600-57ff0a0875dd"],
 " means that the frequency bands of the two signals have to overlap or they \
simply won\[CloseCurlyQuote]t interfere.\n\nAdditionally, the product of the \
two fields means that the ",
 StyleBox["phase",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["difference",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is obtained in addition to the ",
 StyleBox["product of the spectra",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The fact that the phase difference is recovered is vital to the operation \
of a white light interferometer.\n\nMirrors and other optics can impart \
spectral phase to the fields so a calibration must be done to remove phase \
differences caused by the device itself. After calibrating phase differences \
from the device, a nominally transparent material can be placed in one arm of \
the interferometer. Then any phase difference between the two fields in the \
interferometer is only the phase imparted by the material. This means that \
the dispersion of transparent materials can be recovered using scanning white \
light interferometry."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.872001102412904*^9, 3.872001126638975*^9}, {
   3.8720011703984747`*^9, 3.8720011789854603`*^9}, {3.872001212007206*^9, 
   3.8720013315800333`*^9}, {3.8720015089673567`*^9, 3.872001543765472*^9}, {
   3.8720019560947657`*^9, 3.872001957025125*^9}, {3.8720026039865313`*^9, 
   3.872002612919375*^9}, {3.872002666912366*^9, 3.872002676919813*^9}, {
   3.872002709613522*^9, 3.8720027186286*^9}, {3.872002785630632*^9, 
   3.872002834309259*^9}, {3.87200326280151*^9, 3.8720033376529408`*^9}, {
   3.87202266474014*^9, 3.8720227358292437`*^9}, {3.872023128368306*^9, 
   3.8720231285846643`*^9}, {3.872070561400832*^9, 3.872070617143353*^9}, 
   3.8720706568855743`*^9, {3.872070806858032*^9, 3.872070847325025*^9}, {
   3.872071064151536*^9, 3.8720711006255293`*^9}, {3.872071153491111*^9, 
   3.872071171055188*^9}, {3.872071203729786*^9, 
   3.872071205634254*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2071097e-0b7a-42f0-9f33-\
3c120bc7876a"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Deliverable", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755282425706918*^9, 
  3.7552824275818157`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d2f0ac24-a6c2-41f7-a15d-\
1e6e5941abc2"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Using the electric fields provided with this \
assignment generate the following plot, comprised of 4 plots",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.872548827401361*^9, 3.872551371346652*^9, {3.8725865467724733`*^9, 
   3.872586555996142*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"35acb035-b2de-4065-b7a4-\
2940c55d0d85"],

