"Input",ExpressionUUID->"f88fb14f-532f-48d0-bbb4-52f8aa8c4583"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.872023376082779*^9, 3.872023426264682*^9}, {
  3.872023548761046*^9, 3.8720236971208487`*^9}, {3.872023825400907*^9, 
  3.872023867899767*^9}, {3.872024004030272*^9, 3.87202403658062*^9}, {
  3.872024077172963*^9, 3.8720241447717648`*^9}, {3.8725483622093163`*^9, 
  3.872548426009665*^9}, {3.872548474443372*^9, 3.872548474571636*^9}, {
  3.872548531807885*^9, 3.8725486183322077`*^9}, {3.8725487572899513`*^9, 
  3.87254876439458*^9}, {3.872548810565982*^9, 3.8725488259624977`*^9}, {
  3.8725489795862703`*^9, 3.872548979777526*^9}, {3.872549114682746*^9, 
  3.872549114841217*^9}, {3.872552131956696*^9, 
  3.872552132115035*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"060a3995-56c7-488e-83fb-\
b711a96c7feb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["The plots show (counting clockwise from top left):",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n1. Real part of both time domain electric fields (on same plot) [red, \
blue]\n2. Circular cross-correlation of these fields\n3. Fourier transform of \
the correlation\n4. Spectrum [blue solid] and phase [black and dashed green] \
of spectral domain electric field\n\nNote that the reconstruction process \
i.e., the Fourier transform from correlation to frequency space, produces two \
copies of the frequency domain product field [Plot 3] above e.g.,\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
      RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
       RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "*"]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "1"], "(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "*"], 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox["A", "~"], "2"], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", "\[Omega]"}], "-", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e74f8d2d-5653-4f4e-9fc0-229a4dd1507a"],
 "\n\nYou should show only one spectral amplitude and one spectral phase \
[Plot 4]. In this assignment, you will assume that the electric fields \
provided differ only by phase, and have the same amplitudes."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.872548817191832*^9, {3.872549035404063*^9, 3.8725490405583487`*^9}, {
   3.87254913637929*^9, 3.872549146716112*^9}, {3.872549255528561*^9, 
   3.8725492991303787`*^9}, {3.8725493393357687`*^9, 3.872549485187804*^9}, {
   3.8725496570949717`*^9, 3.872549702459426*^9}, {3.872549795209592*^9, 
   3.872549798753611*^9}, {3.872552083755446*^9, 3.8725520845237923`*^9}, {
   3.872586574222827*^9, 3.8725865930761213`*^9}, 
   3.872586660263809*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b3d6ddaf-70cb-4982-a570-\
0b6358dd9d2b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Polynomial fit to the phase:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\nYou will fit an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["n", "th"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "710f8c1b-f655-4cb7-aeb0-a32083754900"],
 " order polynomial to the spectral phase you recover. The spectral phase may \
be represented by its Taylor series expansion about ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "=", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "865b3e8b-140e-40b6-ad64-f405c6d889a1"],
 ":\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[CurlyPhi]", "(", 
     RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "\[TildeTilde]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[CurlyPhi]", "(", "0", ")"}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "\[Omega]"], 
       RowBox[{"\[CurlyPhi]", "(", "0", ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", "2"], 
      RowBox[{
       SubsuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "\[Omega]", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"\[CurlyPhi]", "(", "0", ")"}]}], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "2"]}], "+", "\[Ellipsis]", 
     "+", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       RowBox[{"n", "!"}]], 
      RowBox[{
       SubsuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "\[Omega]", "n"], 
       RowBox[{"\[CurlyPhi]", "(", "0", ")"}]}], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "-", 
         SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"]}], ")"}], "n"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "af0da27b-33e1-489f-a132-fbaad94e838b"],
 "\n\nIn this case, the second order coefficient ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["\[PartialD]", "\[Omega]", "2"], 
    RowBox[{"\[CurlyPhi]", "(", "0", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"da0e836b-8aa3-4c1a-a0fb-6d955907d6df"],
 " is known as the Group Delay Dispersion (GDD) in units of  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["fs", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "8272016a-f0ef-4e06-a0f5-5f1e1a82009a"],
 ". Assume the phase difference is due to the dispersion of a 1 mm thick \
window placed in one arm of the white light interferometer. Match the value \
of your second order coefficient (from your polynomial fit) to one of the \
materials in the \[OpenCurlyQuote]popular optical glasses\[CloseCurlyQuote] \
section on refractiveindex.info. ",
 StyleBox["Report what material the window is made from",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". ",
 StyleBox["Also report the ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["R", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"c2da5297-66e1-44aa-ac36-d654b322c82d"],
 StyleBox[" value from your fit.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\nNote: Group Velocity Dispersion (GVD) is the GDD per millimeter e.g., \
GVD [=] GDD/mm"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8725498078782797`*^9, 3.872549822293116*^9}, {
  3.872549859005796*^9, 3.872549893112952*^9}, {3.872549934551993*^9, 
  3.8725499889431667`*^9}, {3.8725500212252913`*^9, 3.872550100941594*^9}, {
  3.872550149152096*^9, 3.8725501778566523`*^9}, {3.872550220278243*^9, 
  3.87255022831279*^9}, {3.872550278936995*^9, 3.872550279069682*^9}, {
  3.872550378598796*^9, 3.872550480232581*^9}, {3.87255052333916*^9, 
  3.872550614462172*^9}, {3.872550659479619*^9, 3.872550756166883*^9}, {
  3.8725507958398743`*^9, 3.8725508729568243`*^9}, {3.872550912734077*^9, 
  3.872550934015658*^9}, {3.8725511575707912`*^9, 3.872551177180189*^9}, {
  3.872551693525859*^9, 3.872551735480233*^9}, {3.872552908613401*^9, 
  3.872552942607129*^9}, {3.8725866993724833`*^9, 3.872586700102131*^9}, {
  3.872586864638945*^9, 
  3.872586865328966*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"561109d6-a0e8-44ed-ae12-\
2a7dca8fbb19"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Answer the following questions:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n1. Comment on the structure of the reconstructed, frequency-dependent \
field given the two time dependent fields supplied to you with this exercise. \
Specifically, provide an explanation for the seemingly random appearance of \
the time dependent fields, given your reconstruction.\n\n2. Provide an \
explanation for the asymmetry of the cross-correlation function.\n\n3. \
Propose an explanation for the relative strengths of the polynomial \
coefficients from your fit. Specifically, comment on the fact that the \
dominant term is parabolic given the experimental configuration."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.872549800032353*^9, {3.872551001609499*^9, 3.8725510049814043`*^9}, {
   3.872551395122333*^9, 3.8725514826135187`*^9}, {3.8725868880107803`*^9, 
   3.8725869093181553`*^9}, {3.8725869923987103`*^9, 3.872587023677559*^9}, {
   3.8725870697289*^9, 3.8725870998924303`*^9}, {3.8725871447793913`*^9, 
   3.8725871529603157`*^9}, {3.872587202710669*^9, 
   3.872587202998143*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f1946c5a-f917-4361-b055-\
8ab73c898c1b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Grading Rubric", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755274836318931*^9, 3.755274837259777*^9}, {
  3.755282553845039*^9, 
  3.7552825546290617`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"da08676c-8661-4476-bb1c-\
bf4566acf7c4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[GridBox[{
    {Cell["PHGN515 Rubric",
      FontWeight->Bold,ExpressionUUID->
      "95bc2900-4804-4d66-9396-74f4d02d2562"], Cell["Far Exceeds Expectations",
      FontWeight->Bold,ExpressionUUID->
      "78711f66-f941-49ec-bb27-a11a4bea7f1f"], Cell["Exceeds Expectations",
      FontWeight->Bold,ExpressionUUID->
      "13ddf5e3-2789-447c-b2d8-bdb3d593a28b"], Cell["Meets Expectations",
      FontWeight->Bold,ExpressionUUID->
      "ce25375c-4a5a-4ff4-b9ae-98ed44a31b90"], Cell[
     "Partially Meets Expectations",
      FontWeight->Bold,ExpressionUUID->
      "3a1a0e63-13b8-471c-bcba-eec373b680c5"], Cell[
     "Does Not Meet Expectations",
      FontWeight->Bold,ExpressionUUID->
      "c7801914-d388-4570-ae7a-369af1379e54"]},
    {Cell[
     "Grade Value",ExpressionUUID->"d54d63bb-ec43-431d-8ec3-f5e806d6299c"], 
     Cell["[5]",ExpressionUUID->"c4a393c4-7aeb-40be-b09a-f9035fe08175"], Cell[
     "[4]",ExpressionUUID->"230d6ded-da3a-4979-a4b8-33fe89eda9d4"], Cell[
     "[3]",ExpressionUUID->"3e6a87d1-39ea-4136-b6b4-1748f7203f93"], Cell[
     "[2]",ExpressionUUID->"6595604e-4f5f-4d2c-bb82-9bb1b6e00c59"], Cell[
     "[1]",ExpressionUUID->"0e7fbfe1-3ca6-4bc9-9d8c-5eb86c328f19"]},
    {Cell[
     "Support & Evidence",ExpressionUUID->
      "0d956365-70dc-480f-b4a2-cf0fa3db2277"], Cell[TextData[{
      StyleBox["Four plots showing:",
       FontWeight->"Bold"],
      "\n1. Real part of both time domain electric fields\n2. \
Cross-correlation from these fields\n3. Fourier transform of correlation\n4. \
Spectrum and phase\n",
      StyleBox["Superior execution entials:",
