Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Code Outline (pseudo-code)", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755274445590074*^9, 
  3.7552744559729652`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ea925fbd-ccb5-495e-b526-\
f82ac3c7a28f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "1. Calculate circular cross-correlation of provided electric fields\n2. \
Calculate frequency grid from provided temporal grid using the relation\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", "\[Omega]"}], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]"}], 
     RowBox[{"N", " ", 
      RowBox[{"\[DifferentialD]", "t"}]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "05b1c5eb-bcac-4ebc-a2a0-11130cea6290"],
 ", where N is the number of points\n3. Fourier transform correlation signal \
to produce frequency domain field\n4. Extract the phase and amplitude of one \
of the two frequency domain signals\n5. Fit an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["n", "th"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "e7c6ab0b-f51c-4cb2-9b59-9194f9df8af0"],
 " order polynomial to the phase where the amplitude is above some threshold\n\
",
 StyleBox["[Hint: The phase of a function is not very meaningful when the \
function is zero or close to zero]",
  FontSize->10,
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 "\n6. Calculate the GDD from the second order coefficient and match with a \
material on refractiveindex.info\n7. Calculate the second moment, skewness, \
and kurtosis of spectrum"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7552892047917*^9, 3.75528930458457*^9}, {
  3.755289365374763*^9, 3.7552893903903217`*^9}, {3.755290236954488*^9, 
  3.755290239781398*^9}, {3.872551506093153*^9, 3.872551677291059*^9}, {
  3.872551723630128*^9, 3.8725517612114067`*^9}, {3.872551862337413*^9, 
  3.872551869210803*^9}, {3.872553077287291*^9, 3.872553093433098*^9}, {
  3.872553129612064*^9, 3.872553145275313*^9}, {3.872553189021834*^9, 
  3.872553202192113*^9}, {3.87258725258427*^9, 3.872587253507457*^9}, {
  3.872587762190132*^9, 
  3.8725877921128902`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7a3c877c-d6e4-4059-9e62-\
92d9a74cffb4"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
